<div class="bg-sakura-200 bg-pink-sakura p-10 text-white">
  <section
    class="text-sakura-900 container mx-auto flex max-w-3xl flex-col gap-10 rounded-xl bg-white p-10"
  >
    <h1 class="text-center text-2xl font-semibold md:text-3xl">
      Editor's Note
    </h1>
    <div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-3xl flex-col gap-5">
      <p>
        It all started with watching VTubers play games. I watched them panic as
        carefully built houses accidentally caught fire, feel heartbroken after
        losing a cat they had found during an adventure, celebrate the arrival
        of new friends, and proudly show off their first ocean discoveries and
        tridents.
      </p>
      <p>
        I watched a small settlement of just a few people gradually grow into a
        thriving community. Along the way, they hosted Halloween celebrations,
        Christmas events, sports festivals, and countless memorable moments
        together.
      </p>
      <p>
        Virtual worlds have always been one of my dreams. When I was younger, I
        imagined a future where fully immersive virtual reality might become
        possible, and that dream was one of the reasons I chose Computer Science
        over Graphic Design. Back then, I wanted to create AI that could
        understand people, not just intelligent machines, but something capable
        of emotion and connection. In a way, that dream is also why I became
        interested in VTubers. While they are not AI, every performer brings
        their character to life with personality, expression, and warmth. They
        remind me of the kind of digital beings I once imagined.
      </p>
      <p>
        After months of watching Minecraft streams, I began planning a world of
        my own, its purpose, its atmosphere, and what it could become.
        Eventually, I decided to create a virtual world.
      </p>
      <ul class="border-sakura-200 flex flex-col gap-2 border-l-2 pl-5 italic">
        <li>A world where friends can gather.</li>
        <li>A world where imagination can run free.</li>
        <li>A world where people can take a short break from reality.</li>
        <li>
          And a world that can preserve memories across time and distance.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

